# Level 2 - Task 3: K-Means Clustering Analysis

## Project Overview
This project implements K-Means Clustering on the Iris dataset using Python and Scikit-learn. The task focuses on grouping similar data points based on feature similarities using unsupervised machine learning techniques.

## Objectives
- Standardize dataset features
- Apply K-Means clustering
- Determine optimal clusters using the Elbow Method
- Visualize clusters using PCA and scatter plots
- Save generated outputs

## Tools & Libraries
- Python
- Pandas
- NumPy
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn
- Scikit-learn

## Project Workflow
1. Load Iris dataset
2. Standardize features using StandardScaler
3. Use Elbow Method to determine optimal K
4. Apply K-Means clustering
5. Reduce dimensions using PCA
6. Visualize clusters
7. Save outputs

## Outputs
- elbow_method.png
- kmeans_clusters.png
- iris_clustered_data.csv

## Conclusion
The project successfully demonstrated unsupervised clustering using K-Means. The elbow method identified 3 optimal clusters, while PCA enabled effective visualization of clustered data points.
